@ThinkingandTinkering I built up your rig but used high speed 1N914 diodes.
I managed to get over 2V  but if loaded with 1Mohm resistor the voltage dropped to 1V i.e onlt 1 microwatt of power available. 
I put a scope onto the antennae input and saw about 2Vp-p at 50Hz in the input. This is just stray fields you see adjacent to any mains cable. If you wish I can send a photo of the oscilloscope display
